  celestialBodyName: Mercury
  celestialBodyType: Terrestrial
  description: "The smallest and closest planet to the Sun. Mercury is a scarred,
    cratered world with no atmosphere to trap heat, causing temperatures to wildly
    swing from a scorching 430\xB0C during the day to a freezing -180\xB0C at night.
    A year on Mercury lasts just 88 Earth days."
