  celestialBodyType: Terrestrial
  description: Often called Earth's twin due to its similar size, Venus is a runaway
    greenhouse world. It is choked by a thick, toxic atmosphere of carbon dioxide
    and yellowish clouds of sulfuric acid. It is the hottest planet in our solar
    system, with surface temperatures hot enough to melt lead.
